reviews.headline: Long-wear, full coverage foundation with all the benefits! ‚ú®
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] The Charlotte Tilbury Airbrush Flawless Foundation is quite the game-changer! I received Shade 15 Neutral, which is darker than my usual shade (I'm more of a 3 Warm), but I made it work ‚Äî who doesn't love a good contour moment? Let's talk about the foundation itself. It's a long-wear, full coverage gem that feels super lightweight on the skin. Seriously, it's like I'm not even wearing anything! The 7-in-1 features are intriguing: it tackles blemishes, fine lines, and even dark circles. And that smoothing, blurring effect? Yes, please! It gives that gorgeous, powder-matte finish that's perfect for daily wear. Oh, and did I mention it protects against urban pollution? How cool is that? Plus, it's sweatproof, making it an ideal companion for hot days or those intense makeup sessions.

reviews.headline: Favorite
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] CT Air Brush Flawless Foundation is amazing.    It literally smoothes out my skin and covers redness, pores, and fine lines after ONE layer! It's sweat proof/humidity proof. It has powder blur technology and a second skin biometric/phytoyouth essence. Made to last day and night! FULL COVERAGE! Paired with air brush setting spray, it's magic.

reviews.headline: High end
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Overall, beautiful packaging, high-end glass nice pump gives you the perfect amount of product. A little bit does go a long way as long as you have the right skin care primer. There isn't really a sense. The finish is very thick and a dry finish that lasts for a very long time if you have a grease here or already more of a hydrated skin type I think this would work wonderful.

reviews.headline: Loved it
reviews.comments: I really liked the new version of this foundation. It feels softer, more natural and still has great coverage and finish. It's very well packaged and what I liked most is that it doesn't have a strong scent.

reviews.headline: Great Coverage and Lightweight
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I tried the Charlotte Tilbury Airbrush Flawless Foundation in shade 9 Warm, and while it runs a little bit too dark for my skin tone, the formula itself is amazing. It blends smoothly, feels lightweight, and gives me that flawless matte finish that lasts all day without looking cakey. Even though the shade isn't a perfect match, I can make it work with some concealer and powder, and I still love how polished it makes my skin look.

reviews.headline: Nice full coverage option
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Really nice full coverage foundation. Still feels lightweight on the skin and blends really well. The packing is nice and I love a foundation with a pump to control the amount applied each use. Photographs really well too.

reviews.headline: I highly recommend it
reviews.comments: The Airbrush Flawless Foundation in Shade 9 Warm is a truly amazing product. Although I believe I chose a shade that doesn't quite match my skin tone, I'm still very impressed. The formula works beautifully on my skin, it blends well, feels smooth, and gives a flawless finish. My skin looks noticeably better after applying it, with a soft, airbrushed effect. Even though the shade isn't perfect for me, I plan to continue using it creatively. It's that good! I highly recommend it for its performance and skin-enhancing results.

reviews.headline: Blurred finish
reviews.comments: I love how this was easily applied to my skin and looked like a second skin rather than a product sitting on my face. It took away my redness and left me blurred. Loved my look. This was gifted by Charlotte Tilbury in exchange for my honest review.

reviews.headline: Full coverage
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I love the pump packaging of this foundation. The coverage is full with a matte finish. I apply this with a brush so it applies and blends out evenly. It wears well, lasting all day.

reviews.headline: Would purchase again and again
reviews.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] The Charlotte Tilbury Airbrush Flawless Foundation is hands down one of the best foundations I've ever used! The coverage is absolutely flawless‚Äîsmooth, even, and completely full without feeling heavy or cakey. It really does what it promises: blurs imperfections, evens out skin tone, and gives my complexion that airbrushed finish.

I love how lightweight it feels, yet it lasts all day (and night!) without breaking apart or getting oily. I wore it through a long day and it stayed put beautifully with no need for touch-ups. The shade match (9 Warm) is perfect, blending seamlessly with my skin for a natural but polished look.

Another huge plus is how it photographs‚Äîit gives that soft, flawless glow without any flashback. Perfect for both everyday wear and special occasions.

If you're looking for a foundation that delivers full coverage, long-lasting wear, and a skin-like finish, this is it. Worth every penny!

reviews.headline: Thick thick thick
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I unfortunately messed up selecting my shade based off of their color chart, and this is much too light for my end of summer skin.  However I tested the longevity on my hand. After leaving it on for an entire day, it was still there and actually difficult to wash off. It left a film of color after my usual cleansing, which is annoying. This makeup is THICK.  Personally, for daily wear it is much too thick and settles into cracks.  This would be great performance makeup, or if you felt you would be sweating a lot because it doesn't budge.

reviews.headline: Great coverage
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I love this foundation, you can see in my photo that I've applied it above the red line and it does give my skin more of a solid color. Below the red line, you can see all the different pigments and freckles. This stuff works!

reviews.headline: So beautiful!
reviews.comments:
I received the Charlotte Tilbury
Airbrush Flawless Foundation (Shade
4 Neutral) complimentary for my honest review. I am really impressed with this full coverage foundation! The packing is super cute with the gold top. The pump feature makes it's very easy to apply the right amount without waste. The formula is so creamy for a fully liquid foundation. It blends so well with a beauty blender. It is full coverage that dries matte. You can build this up to the right coverage for you. It has 7-in-1 properties. My favorite feature is that it totally covers redness and pores. You end up with a beautiful blue effect. It helps with issues including hyperpigmentation and dark circles as well. The shade is perfect for fair skin. The Powder Blur Airtech formula really does leave you looking airbrushed. It's absolutely stunning!

reviews.headline: Flawless Look
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Charlotte Tilbury's Airbrush Flawless Foundation in Shade 5 Neutral gives serious full coverage with a smooth, blurred finish that really lives up to the name. It lasts all day without much transfer, which I love. The shade is a fair-medium neutral, though it can lean a little warm on some skin tones. It is definitely matte, so if you have dry skin you'll want to prep well. Overall, a great long-wear foundation if you like a polished, flawless look.

reviews.headline: Tone evened
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Charlotte Tilbury's Airbrush Flawless Foundation is an ideal choice for my skin type. It offers full coverage without feeling heavy, akin to a soft-focus filter in a bottle. This foundation effectively smooths out pores, evens skin tone, and provides a velvety finish that lasts throughout the day. As someone with combination skin, I didn't even require primer. It sets quickly, so I suggest working in sections. Whether you're taking photos, attending an event, or simply want to feel flawless on a regular day, this foundation is a must-have.

reviews.headline: Sun-kissed
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Charlotte Tilbury airbrush flawless foundation is quality and a great option to leave your skin looking sun-kissed. I would personally need a different shade this time of year but as you can see it blended well, was easy to use and left my hand looking bronze as if it was kissed by the sun. I plan to try a few other shades for the perfect match.

faceoff_positive.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Charlotte Tilbury Airbrush Foundation in shade 4 Neutral is a solid everyday option that blends well and feels lightweight on the skin. The shade 4 Neutral is fairly forgiving for anyone with a neutral undertone, reading neither too pink nor too warm on most days. The formula offers a nice balance between coverage and translucency, giving a natural finish that still smooths over minor imperfections. On first application, the product glides with a creamy texture and sets down without heavy tackiness, which helps it wear comfortably for hours. The pump dispenser is convenient, yielding the right amount of product with minimal waste and reducing mess in the morning routine. I appreciate how buildable the coverage is; a light layer covers uneven skin tone, while a second layer can address translucency in the center of the face without looking cakey. The finish sits somewhere between satin and dewy, catching light nicely without enhancing fine lines or texture too aggressively. In terms of longevity, it wears well throughout the day, especially when applied over a suitable primer and sealed with a light powder in hotter weather. The texture blur is noticeable, thanks to the foundation's ability to diffuse minor imperfections without emphasizing pores. However, it can cling slightly to dryer patches if skin isn't exfoliated or moisturized properly, so a good skincare base is key. I've found it to layer nicely with bronzer and minimal blush, maintaining a cohesive complexion without muddying shades. Color-matching with shade 4 Neutral generally remains stable across different lighting, though under very bright light it can appear marginally lighter than expected on deeper skin tones. The packaging feels premium and Instagram-worthy, which makes it a pleasure to display on vanity or in a makeup bag. Cleanup after removal is straightforward, and the formula doesn't leave behind a heavy residue that makes skin feel congested. Overall, this shade and finish offer a reliable, polished look suitable for work, days out, or casual filming environments. For those seeking more luminous glow, a light application of a radiant primer or a subtle highlighter on the high points can enhance dimensionality without overpowering the base. The foundation performs best when your skincare is in good condition and your tools are clean, ensuring a smooth, even spread. If you're new to Charlotte Tilbury, this shade provides a gentle introduction to the brand's approach to perfected but approachable skin finishes. In short, 4 Neutral is a versatile, easy-to-use shade with a balanced finish that flatters many undertones and offers dependable wear across a standard day.
faceoff_positive.headline: great foundation

faceoff_negative.comments: I was excited to try this foundation since I've enjoyed other foundations from Charlotte Tilbury but unfortunately this is one where from afar your skin might look good but up close it's cakey, powdery, and dry looking. You'll definitely tell someone's wearing foundation with this. I applied it with a brush and smoothed it with a velour puff. It looks much better on camera than in person. I think it'd be a good one to wear for photographs or stage performances since it has a very full coverage effect and is matte. Up close it's just not flattering. Maybe someone with oily skin would enjoy this more since it is more on the dry side naturally. Shade wise I have 4 Neutral but I think 4 or 5 cool would have been better but my rating is not based on shade match since I didn't have those shades as options at the time. The bottle is very pretty and well designed. It feels appropriate for the price point. This foundation was gifted to me for review.
faceoff_negative.headline: Too dry and cakey
